hashSearch

public static int hashSearch(Binding[] table,
                             int log2Size,
                             int mask,
                             java.lang.String key,
                             int hash)
Search a hash table using double hashing and open addressing.
Parameters:
table - the hash table
log2Size - log2 of the (used) size of table
mask - must equal ((1 << log2Size) - 1)
key - the search key
hash - the hash of the search key
Returns:
the index of the element in table containing the match (such that table[index].getName()==key); if there is no such element, returns an index such that (table[index]==null || tabel[index]==DELETED).

getFunctionValue

public final java.lang.Object getFunctionValue()
Get value of "function binding" of a Binding. Some languages (including Common Lisp and Emacs Lisp) associate both a value binding and a function binding with a symbol.
Throws:
UnboundSymbol - if no function binding.

getFunctionValue

public final java.lang.Object getFunctionValue(java.lang.Object defaultValue)
Get value of "function binding" of a Binding. Some languages (including Common Lisp and Emacs Lisp) associate both a value binding and a function binding with a symbol.
Parameters:
defaultValue - value to return if there is no function binding
Returns:
the function value, or defaultValue if no function binding.
